<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-05-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="227" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d227">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Porter</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-05-15"><hi rend="italic">May 15,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Porter</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Ambassador, Paris:</hi></p>
                        <p>Ex-President Harrison expected arrive in France about Wednesday, 24. Have
                            authorities notified, so that any proper courtesies may be extended.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>